The paper discusses the implementation of hardware neural networks based on coupled oscillator networks, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of emerging nanotechnologies suggests a focus on electronic devices and circuits, which could fall under the categories of electronics (cs.ET) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The paper also discusses signal processing and pattern recognition, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
